{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-03316/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-03316"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:33:16"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tracking, pan"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["three shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman sits next to the couple and speaks with the man."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03316/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-03316","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03316/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-03316"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03316/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03316/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03316/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03316/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03316/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03316/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03316/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03316/canvas/1/ed6c120f-d7e6-49c6-80db-050a432c6221","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T14:09:59.812Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds has ordered a steak tartare for Cyril and jokes with her, calling her a “carnivore.” This French dish consists of seasoned raw ground beef, often served with a raw egg yolk. It is therefore, indeed, quite carnivorous. On a symbolic level, though, it emphasizes Cyril’s willingness to do battle with anyone, whether it be her brother or Alma. She has animal instincts.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03316/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:646.2135922330096,224.66019417475724,318.44660194174764,295.14563106796123"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03316/canvas/1/b1512ca2-9d22-4ea5-a303-ebb51f0bba88","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T14:10:36.513Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Cyril mentions Reynolds’s “favorite client”—Barbara Rose—who will be seen in the film shortly. The character of Rose is based on Barabara Woolworth Hutton. Known as “Poor Little Rich Girl” for the extravagant debutante ball her father, retail tycoon Frank Winfield Woolworth, threw for her during the Great Depression, Hutton would go on to marry seven times and lead a troubled life due to drinking, drugs, and husbands with ulterior motives. She was a major client of Spanish designer Cristóbal Balenciaga: “In one day she ordered twenty-nine outfits from Florette [Balenciaga’s lead saleswoman], another day it was thirty-one. She had total recall of every collection and never needed to see a dress twice. The fittings took place in her second-floor suite at the Ritz, the grandest the hotel had” (Blume, <em>The Master of Us All</em>, 117).</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03316/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1197.6699029126212,156.31067961165047,361.94174757281576,347.96116504854365"}}}]}]}]}